description: Situated in a circle, tall poles hold aloft a canopy of ropes laden with vibrant paper-shaded lanterns that sway gently in the breeze as it rolls off the nearby river.  Outside of the circle, a small band of string and pipe players create lively tunes for dancing, as onlookers gather near to hear the music.

Situated in a circle, tall poles hold aloft a canopy of ropes laden with vibrant paper-shaded lanterns to create a picturesque scene backed by the gentle whisper of the river.  Outside of the circle, a small band of string and pipe players weave together song after song, while on the other side of the Tempest fireworks burst into the sky, one colorful blossom after another.
title: [River's Rest, Festival Grounds]
